        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 4:55PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 454 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Freer, moving northwest at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Freer.

This includes US Highway 59 between mile markers 764 and 778.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
